main event: A witness reported seeing a fiery object that almost hit the ground near Ellsworth Air Force Base in South Dakota on September 21, 1964.
interesting points: The object was brighter than a meteor and had a long trail.
The witness reported seeing the object at around 8:00 PM local time.
The report was filed by the Deputy Director of Information at Ellsworth Air Force Base.
The report was sent to the Air Force Systems Command's Foreign Technology Division at Wright-Patterson Air Force Base.
The report states that the information given was not sufficient to determine exactly what the object was, and that there were no other reports of this incident.
location: Ellsworth Air Force Base, South Dakota
